3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a novel approach to solving optimization problems using machine learning techniques. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a potential category as the paper deals with motion estimation, which is a common problem in robotics. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the proposed method is a neural network-based approach.
